Iings (Likeyenge Hengi). Especially when it came to books! I would spend hours and hours at the public library with my library card, irregardless of the book medium (e-reader, hardcopy, or kindle). In another forum, I explained my love for books and how I bring different books to reading-night. At one point, I even managed to make a somehow unreasonable analogy about it, but blanking out on the details! I think I’ll go with something simple this time, so the words do not get lost on translation. Simply put, I love it*.

So personally, it makes no sense for me to want to see it change!

* Yes indeed, it may sound unethical to, like, engulf the technology in designed-successful form, without feeding back the test result of what you actually think. Slowly consuming thoughts and also fissioning flesh. Great. It’s a podcast. Don’t judge me.
